canonical:
  title: 賀皇太子封冊箋
  author: 李達衷
  language: lzh
  text: 正位居仁光膺寶冊推恩布德誕告多方天下交欣宗支益固云云禀資純粹處事剛明厚澤旁霑群情係乎主器英謨深造重事宜其擅權雖兆民慶賴之悉均予小子賀悰之彌篤云云頃叨宿衛優荷寵榮守職東邦喜先覩重輪之日馳心北極庶幾裨肯構之基
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 賀皇太子封冊箋
  author: 李達衷
  language: lzh
  text: 正位居仁。光膺寶冊。推恩布德。誕告多方。天下交欣。宗支益固。云云。禀資純粹。處事剛明。厚澤旁霑。群情係乎主器。英謨深造。重事宜其擅權。雖兆民慶賴之悉均。予小子賀悰之彌篤。云云。頃叨宿衛。優荷寵榮。守職東邦。喜先覩重輪之日。馳心北極。庶幾裨肯構之基。
korean:
  title: 하 황태자 봉책 전
  author: 이달충
  language: kor
  text: 위(位)를 바로잡고 인(仁)에 거(居)하여 영광스레 보위(寶位)를 받으시고, 은(恩)을 밀고 덕을 반포하여 이에 다방(多方)에 고하오니, 천하가 모두 기뻐하고 종지(宗支)가 더욱 완고하옵나이다. 운운. 품자(稟資)가 순수하시고 처사(處事)가 강명(剛明)하시어, 두터운 은택(恩澤)이 널리 적시오니 군정(群情)이 모두 인주(人主)의 그릇임을 촉망하옵고, 영명(英明)하신 계책이 깊은 데 이르오니, 중사(重事)는 천권(擅權)하심이 마땅하옵니다. 이에 만민(萬民)이 경사로 여겨 의지함이 모두 고르에 힘입어 소자(小子)인 저의 하례하는 정성이 더욱 돈독하도소이다. 운운. 앞서 외람되이 숙위(宿衛)로서 흠뻑 총영(寵榮)을 받자왔더니, 이제 동방(東邦)에 구실을 지키면서 중륜(重輪)의 해[日]를 먼저 뵈옴을 기뻐하오며, 북두(北斗)에 마음을 달려 긍구(肯構)의 터를 도와 드리기를 원하옵나이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0350_010_0270&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Memorial Celebrating the Investiture of the Crown Prince
  author: Lee Dal-chung
  language: eng
  text: |-
    In righteousness he establishes his seat, in benevolence he abides,
    Receiving with splendor the imperial seal and its sacred grace.
    Spread forth is favor, broadcast is virtue—
    Thus proclaimed to the myriad regions, all hearts turn in joy,
    The royal lineage grows ever more steadfast.

    Inheriting a nature pure and refined,
    In all matters displaying strength and luminous wisdom,
    His generous bounty falls upon all like rain—
    The people's hearts are lifted by his fitness to bear the realm.
    Deep runs his sagacious counsel, reaching far,
    It is fitting that he exercise authority over grave affairs.
    Though ten thousand folk receive this blessing in equal measure,
    My small gratitude swells all the more sincere.

    Once I served humbly in the palace guard,
    Bathed in favor and honored by your grace.
    Now stationed in the eastern realm, I stand at my post,
    Joyful to witness first the rising of that resplendent orb.
    My heart races toward the northern star,
    Eager to aid in laying the foundation of your glorious works.
  footnotes:
    - '"重輪" (heavy wheels) is a classical metaphor for the sun, symbolizing imperial authority and brilliance.'
    - '"北極" (North Pole) refers to the ruling sovereign, with the author positioning himself in service to the throne.'
    - The repeated "云云" (and so forth) indicates rhetorical flourishes typical of formal memorial documents.
